cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with generative 3D face models and their ability to decouple natural sources of variation, such as identity and expression. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a novel architecture that combines a 3D generator with a 2D discriminator that leverages conventional CNNs, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) further suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also presents a training scheme based on auxiliary classifiers, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with facial shape modeling, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
